  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nA non-trivial attestation aggregation strategy is being developed. Leading up to this, a new topic and aggregation validation has been stipulated in the networking specification: https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/specs/networking/p2p-interface.md#global-topics\r\n\r\nWe need to add the `beacon_aggregate_and_proof` topic along with the required validation. The validation requires knowing past aggregates, including those in past seen blocks. We need to keep track of a cache of these, likely andLRUCache on the `BeaconChain` which gets filled with new blocks and attestations as they are seen.\r\n\r\nFurther, the `committee_index{subnet_id}_beacon_attestion` topics need to be constructed and handled correctly as per the specification.",
